\begin_layout Standard
We have shown results that establish interchanging limits and integrals
 when such limits exist.
 The next result makes a more general statement about interchanging limit
 superiors and inferiors of non-negative measurable functions (which always
 exist in the extended real numbers) with their integrals, although we cannot
 get strict equality.
