\begin_inset Formula 
\[
h_{n}:=\indicate_{\left\{ f\geq\frac{1}{n}\right\} }\leq nf
\]

\end_inset

where both sides are measurable since 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is Borel-measurable.
 By the monotonicity and linearity of the integral, we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mu\left(\left\{ x\in\X\mid f\left(x\right)\geq\frac{1}{n}\right\} \right)=\lebInt{\mu}{h_{n}}\leq n\lebInt{\mu}f=0.
\]

\end_inset

Since 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(x\right)\geq\frac{1}{n}\Longrightarrow f\left(x\right)\geq\frac{1}{n+1}$
\end_inset

